    <summary>Specifies arguments for creating a variant of a typeface.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` is a ref struct that carries the arguments used to request a specific
variant of a typeface from <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)>.
It can specify a font collection index, a named palette, per-color palette overrides,
and a variable font design position.

Because it is a `ref struct`, it cannot be stored on the heap or boxed.

## Examples

```csharp
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    CollectionIndex = 0,
    PaletteIndex = 1,
};
using var clone = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
